# PHASE 2 — IMPLEMENT fix round (triggered by VERIFY finding)

<role>
Fix a VERIFY-reported finding within the authorized surface (`bin/cli.js`, `tests/cli.test.js`). Do not touch anything else.
</role>

<finding_to_fix>
id: format-duplicate-unsupported
rule_id: spec.unsupported-format-not-rejected
severity: MEDIUM (verdict-binding)
file: bin/cli.js, line 45 (the `parseVersionFormat` function)

`const idx = argv.indexOf('--format');` inspects only the FIRST occurrence of `--format` in argv. Repro: `node bin/cli.js version --format json --format yaml` exits 0 and prints `{"version":"0.1.0"}` instead of rejecting the unsupported `yaml` value with exit 1. This violates the criteria's requirement: "`--format yaml`, or any `--format` value other than `json`, causes the CLI to exit with status code 1 and print an error."
</finding_to_fix>

<fix_guidance>
Standard CLI convention (and Node's own `util.parseArgs`) is last-flag-wins when a flag is repeated. Change `parseVersionFormat`'s lookup from `argv.indexOf('--format')` to `argv.lastIndexOf('--format')` so the LAST occurrence of `--format` determines the value. This makes `--format json --format yaml` correctly resolve to `yaml` (last one) and exit 1, while keeping the function's existing structure/style (same missing-value check, same error+exit pattern) unchanged. This is a one-line fix.

Do NOT touch `parseNameFlag` (the pre-existing `--name` flag parser used by the unrelated `hello` subcommand) — it is out of scope per the criteria's "Out of Scope" section, even though it has the same first-occurrence pattern. Only `parseVersionFormat` (added by this diff, used only by `version`) is in scope.
</fix_guidance>

<verification>
After your fix, run and confirm:
- `node bin/cli.js version --format json --format yaml` → must exit 1 with an error message (the finding's repro case).
- `node bin/cli.js version --format json` → must still print `{"version":"0.1.0"}` and exit 0 (unchanged).
- `node bin/cli.js version` → must still print `0.1.0` and exit 0 (unchanged).
- `node bin/cli.js version --format yaml` → must still exit 1 (unchanged).
- `npm test` → all existing tests must still pass. Optionally add one regression test in `tests/cli.test.js` for the duplicate-flag case (`run(['version', '--format', 'json', '--format', 'yaml'])` should throw with exit 1) — this is encouraged but not mandatory; keep it minimal if added.
</verification>

<output>
Report your verdict: `PASS` on success; `BLOCKED` if you cannot fix this within `bin/cli.js`/`tests/cli.test.js`. Do not run `git commit`. Only touch `bin/cli.js` and `tests/cli.test.js`.
</output>

Fix the finding now.
